SIMPLE: semicircle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Semicircle
<hw>Sem"i*cir`cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The half of a circle; the part of a circle bounded by
its diameter and half of its circumference.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A
semicircumference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A body in the form of half of a circle, or half of a
circumference.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>An instrument for measuring angles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semicircled</ent>⟦br⟧
